.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5336169978655607e-23, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rider\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"rider\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"the relentlessly undulating course\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"the third and final ascent\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blasting his way past massive crowds and with 50-second advantage by the Montmartre summit, the 24-year-old Belgian seemed comfortably en route to his second road gold in a week.\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1796, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1726, \"end\": 1733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.149028046004699e-13, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his way\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1634}, {\"ngram\": \"massive crowds\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1654}, {\"ngram\": \"50-second advantage\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"the Montmartre summit\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1708}, {\"ngram\": \"route\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"his second road gold\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1785}, {\"ngram\": \"a week\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1795}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The last-minute mechanical could have been fatal to his chances, but the quick change meant Evenepoel could secure his country's second road race title, after Greg van Avermaet in Rio in 2016, in three Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 2013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1956, \"end\": 1973, \"title\