from\": 2727, \"to\": 2735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I got a straight puncture, I had to change bikes and the car wasn't ready for that moment so it was a bit stressy, but in the end, I had time enough.\", \"from\": 2737, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a straight puncture\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2762}, {\"ngram\": \"bikes\", \"from\": 2780, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"the car\", \"from\": 2790, \"to\": 2797}, {\"ngram\": \"that moment\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2826}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2866}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What a day!\\\"\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 2899, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"What a day\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 2897}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A warm, sunny day in France saw the mini-peloton of 90 riders - the smallest ever in Olympic men's road racing - get on their way smoothly, and even before leaving Paris, a break of five containing Eric Manizabayo (Rwanda), Thanakhan Chaiyasombat (Thailand), Mauritian national champion Christopher Rougier-Lagane, Charles Kagimu (Uganda) and sprinter Achraf Ed Doghmy (Morocco) quickly formed.\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 3296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2922, \"end\": 2928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9968804645448817, \"rank\": 0.0031256625369655306, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3066, \"end\": 3071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8696011185640274e-35, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3117, \"end\": 3123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwand