087095, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A warm, sunny day\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2918}, {\"ngram\": \"the mini\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"peloton\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 2949}, {\"ngram\": \"90 riders\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 2962}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic men's road racing\", \"from\": 2986, \"to\": 3011}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"Eric Manizabayo\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3114}, {\"ngram\": \"Christopher Rougier-Lagane\", \"from\": 3188, \"to\": 3214}, {\"ngram\": \"sprinter Achraf Ed Doghmy\", \"from\": 3244, \"to\": 3269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Achraf Ed Doghmy then suffered repeated mechanicals, but time and again he was able to rejoin the other four - a yo-yoing process that continued for almost another 100 kilometres - as they pressed on over the C\\u00f4te des Gardes, the first of 13 classified climbs.\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3559, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Achraf Ed Doghmy\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3314}, {\"ngram\": \"repeated mechanicals\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3349}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 3355, \"to\": 3359}, {\"ngram\": \"the other four - a yo-yoing process\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3427}, {\"ngram\": \"almost another 100 kilometres\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3476}, {\"ngram\": \"the C\\u00f4te des Gardes\", \"from\": 3503, \"to\": 3522}, {\"ngram\": \"13 classified climbs\", \"from\": 3537, \"to\": 3557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile in the peloton, the Danish squad kept a nominal control on affairs, courtesy of Mikkel Bjerg and Michael M\\u00f8rk\\u00f8v.\", \"from\": 3560, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3590, \"end\": 3596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.434413655596919e-15, \"text\": \"Danish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 3650, \"end\": 3662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mikkel_Bjerg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mikkel Bjerg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mikkel_Bjerg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mikkel_Bjerg\"}, {\"begin\": 3667, \"end\": 3681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_M\\u00f8rk\\u00f8v\", \"score\": 0.9999973201401627, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michael M\\u00f8rk\\u00f8v\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_M\\u00f8rk\\u00f8v\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_M\\u00f8rk\\u00f8v\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3584}, {\"ngram\": \"a nominal control\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3625}, {\"ngram\": \"affairs\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3636}, {\"ngram\": \"courtesy\", \"from\": 3638, \"to\": 3646}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of the longest races of the season, the 200km-to-go sign came and went with little change in the overall scenario, barring the four-man breakaway, which was occasionally five whenever Ed Doghmy regained contact, using the broad, well-surfaced country roads outside the French capital to open up their advantage to well over 12 minutes.\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 4026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3960, \"end\": 3966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7085541329387367, \"rank\": 0.40977544988976955, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the longest races\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3711}, {\"ngram\": \"the season\", \"from\": 3715, \"to\": 3725}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200km-to-go sign\", \"from\": 3727, \"to\": 3747}, {\"ngram\": \"little change\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3780}, {\"ngram\": \"the overall scenario\", \"from\": 3784, \"to\": 3804}, {\"ngram\": \"the four-man breakaway\", \"from\": 3814, \"to\": 3836}, {\"ngram\": \"Ed Doghmy\", \"from\": 3875, \"to\": 3884}, {\"ngram\": \"contact\", \"from\": 3894, \"to\": 3901}, {\"ngram\": \"the broad, well-surfaced country roads\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 3947}, {\"ngram\": \"their advantage\", \"from\": 3986, \"to\": 4001}, {\"ngram\": \"well over 12 minutes\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a brief spell of peloton control by Great Britain, with Fred Wright visibly inviting other teams to help, a lack of collaboration and certain passivity in the bunch abruptly saw another long-distant move burst into life.\", \"from\": 4028, \"to\": 4254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4070, \"end\": 4083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9984078814829216, \"rank\": 0.001594652234714316, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 4090, \"end\": 4101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999956969842781, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Wright\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brief spell\", \"from\": 4034, \"to\": 4047}, {\"ngram\": \"peloton control\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4066}, {\"ngram\": \"other teams\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4130}, {\"ngram\": \"a lack\", \"from\": 4140, \"to\": 4146}, {\"ngram\": \"collaboration\", \"from\": 4150, \"to\": 4163}, {\"ngram\": \"certain passivity\", \"from\": 4168, \"to\": 4185}, {\"ngram\": \"the bunch\", \"from\": 4189, \"to\": 4198}, {\"ngram\": \"another long-distant move\", \"from\": 4212, \"to\": 4237}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 4249, \"to\": 4253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gleb Syritsa (Neutral), Ryan Mullen (Ireland), Elia Viviani (Italy) - a former Olympic gold medallist, albeit on the track - and Georgios Bouglas (Greece) suddenly sped away on a straight, exposed segment road, producing absolutely no reaction as they did so.\", \"from\": 4255, \"to\": 4515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4255, \"end\": 4267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gleb_Syritsa\", \"score\": 0.9999999367355505, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gleb Syritsa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gleb_Syritsa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gleb_Syritsa\"}, {\"begin\": 4279, \"end\": 4290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Mullen\", \"score\": 0.9999964357339051, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Mullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Mullen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Mullen\"}, {\"begin\": 4292, \"end\": 4299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998834861023929, \"rank\": 0.00011651553009246908, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 4302, \"end\": 4314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elia Viviani\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elia_Viviani\"}, {\"begin\": 4316, \"end\": 4321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9789286882289896, \"rank\": 0.021524867258827386, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4385, \"end\": 4401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgios_Bouglas\", \"score\": 0.999999495225111, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Georgios Bouglas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgios_Bouglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgios_Bouglas\"}, {\"begin\": 4403, \"end\": 4409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999969876889632, \"rank\": 2.9956594032921224e-06, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Neutral\", \"from\": 4269, \"to\": 4276}, {\"ngram\": \"a former Olympic gold medallist\", \"from\": 4325, \"to\": 4356}, {\"ngram\": \"a straight, exposed segment road\", \"from\": 4432, \"to\": 4464}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely no reaction\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As has been widely commented, the small size of the 2024 Olympic peloton, coupled with the lack of race radios and the almost excessively-long distance of this year's road race, all but ensured such a lethargic start to the race.\", \"from\": 4517, \"to\": 4746, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic peloton\", \"from\": 4565, \"to\": 4589}, {\"ngram\": \"the lack\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4612}, {\"ngram\": \"race radios\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4627}, {\"ngram\": \"the almost excessively-long distance\", \"from\": 4632, \"to\": 4668}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's road race\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4693}, {\"ngram\": \"such a lethargic start\", \"from\": 4711, \"to\": 4733}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 4737, \"to\": 4745}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That said, as soon as the leading break of five pushed out their advantage to just a few seconds over 15 minutes, as if by magic the bunch suddenly snapped into life and began to chase hard.\", \"from\": 4747, \"to\": 4937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the leading break\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4786}, {\"ngram\": \"their advantage\", \"from\": 4806, \"to\": 4821}, {\"ngram\": \"just a few seconds\", \"from\": 4825, \"to\": 4843}, {\"ngram\": \"15 minutes\", \"from\": 4849, \"to\": 4859}, {\"ngram\": \"magic\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4875}, {\"ngram\": \"the bunch\", \"from\": 4876, \"to\": 4885}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 4908, \"to\": 4912}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Powered by an impressive trio of Belgium's Tiesj Benoot, the Netherlands Dan Hoole and Denmark's Bjerg, the peloton quickly sliced away huge chunks of time on the five leaders and four chasers.\", \"from\": 4939, \"to\": 5132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4972, \"end\": 4979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.436398602191839e-12, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 5026, \"end\": 5033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.999999344642889, \"rank\": 6.55357217646797e-07, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an impressive trio\", \"from\": 4950, \"to\": 4968}, {\"ngram\": \"the Netherlands Dan Hoole\", \"from\": 4996, \"to\": 5021}, {\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 5043, \"to\": 5054}, {\"ngram\": \"huge chunks\", \"from\": 5075, \"to\": 5086}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 5090, \"to\": 5094}, {\"ngram\": \"the five leaders\", \"from\": 5098, \"to\": 5114}, {\"ngram\": \"four chasers\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even while riders slowly but surely began to shelled from the back of the main peloton, the increase in speed took its toll ahead, too as Syritsa suddenly sat up on one of the multiple minor ascents with around 140 kilometres to go.\", \"from\": 5133, \"to\": 5365, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5150}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 5191, \"to\": 5199}, {\"ngram\": \"the main peloton\", \"from\": 5203, \"to\": 5219}, {\"ngram\": \"the increase\", \"from\": 5221, \"to\": 5233}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 5237, \"to\": 5242}, {\"ngram\": \"its toll\", \"from\": 5248, \"to\": 5256}, {\"ngram\": \"Syritsa\", \"from\": 5271, \"to\": 5278}, {\"ngram\": \"the multiple minor ascents\", \"from\": 5305, \"to\": 5331}, {\"ngram\": \"around 140 kilometres\", \"from\": 5337, \"to\": 5358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following four fairly humdrum hours, the first significant development in the race's final outcome came when the three surviving counter attackers - Mullen, Viviani and Bouglas - were able to reach the five early breakaways.\", \"from\": 5367, \"to\": 5591, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four fairly humdrum hours\", \"from\": 5377, \"to\": 5402}, {\"ngram\": \"the first significant development\", \"from\": 5404, \"to\": 5437}, {\"ngram\": \"the race's final outcome\", \"from\": 5441, \"to\": 5465}, {\"ngram\": \"the three surviving counter attackers\", \"from\": 5476, \"to\": 5513}, {\"ngram\": \"Mullen\", \"from\": 5516, \"to\": 5522}, {\"ngram\": \"Viviani\", \"from\": 5524, \"to\": 5531}, {\"ngram\": \"Bouglas\", \"from\": 5536, \"to\": 5543}, {\"ngram\": \"the five early breakaways\", \"from\": 5565, \"to\": 5590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By this point the leading move itself was close to disintegration, though, with only Kagamu and Rougier-Lagane managing to keep in contact with a much fresher trio of Mullen, Viviani and Bouglas.\", \"from\": 5592, \"to\": 5787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5759, \"end\": 5765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999998279554495, \"rank\": 1.544359642084208e-07, \"text\": \"Mullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 5595, \"to\": 5605}, {\"ngram\": \"the leading move\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5622}, {\"ngram\": \"disintegration\", \"from\": 5643, \"to\": 5657}, {\"ngram\": \"only Kagamu\", \"from\": 5672, \"to\": 5683}, {\"ngram\": \"Rougier-Lagane\", \"from\": 5688, \"to\": 5702}, {\"ngram\": \"contact\", \"from\": 5723, \"to\": 5730}, {\"ngram\": \"a much fresher trio\", \"from\": 5736, \"to\": 5755}, {\"ngram\": \"Viviani\", \"from\": 5767, \"to\": 5774}, {\"ngram\": \"Bouglas\", \"from\": 5779, \"to\": 5786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bunch itself was growing increasingly restless, meanwhile, and in the first of a quickfire series of six classified climbs, the C\\u00f4te de Senlis, Domen Novak (Slovenia) opened up the late hostilities.\", \"from\": 5789, \"to\": 5991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5929, \"end\": 5935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senlis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.883284108804875e-33, \"text\": \"Senlis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senlis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senlis\"}, {\"begin\": 5950, \"end\": 5958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"score\": 0.999678333617366, \"rank\": 0.000321769885363485, \"text\": \"Slovenia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The bunch\", \"from\": 5789, \"to\": 5798}, {\"ngram\": \"a quickfire series\", \"from\": 5872, \"to\": 5890}, {\"ngram\": \"six classified climbs\", \"from\": 5894, \"to\": 5915}, {\"ngram\": \"Domen Novak\", \"from\": 5937, \"to\": 5948}, {\"ngram\": \"the late hostilities\", \"from\": 5970, \"to\": 5990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't just the secondary actors in the race, either: on the much shorter, twisting, C\\u00f4te d'Herbouvilliers, favourites like Wout van Aert (Belgium) and Julian Alaphilippe (France) began insisting ever-more frequently that their place was on or near the front.\", \"from\": 5992, \"to\": 6254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6119, \"end\": 6132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}, {\"begin\": 6134, \"end\": 6141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.436398602191839e-12, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 6147, \"end\": 6165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Julian Alaphilippe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\"}, {\"begin\": 6167, \"end\": 6173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9968804645448817, \"rank\": 0.0031256625369655306, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just the secondary actors\", \"from\": 6002, \"to\": 6027}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 6031, \"to\": 6039}, {\"ngram\": \"C\\u00f4te d'Herbouvilliers\", \"from\": 6080, \"to\": 6101}, {\"ngram\": \"their place\", \"from\": 6217, \"to\": 6228}, {\"ngram\": \"the front\", \"from\": 6244, \"to\": 6253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then on the Cote de Saint-Remy-Les-Chouvreuse, the first serious challenges materialized in the peloton, most notably when Ben Healy (Ireland) launched a typically sustained attack, 90 kilometres out, drawing out a string of riders behind him.\", \"from\": 6256, \"to\": 6499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6379, \"end\": 6388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0145244429722014e-30, \"text\": \"Ben Healy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\"}, {\"begin\": 6390, \"end\": 6397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998834861023929, \"rank\": 0.00011651553009246908, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Cote de Saint-Remy-Les-Chouvreuse\", \"from\": 6264, \"to\": 6301}, {\"ngram\": \"the first serious challenges\", \"from\": 6303, \"to\": 6331}, {\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 6348, \"to\": 6359}, {\"ngram\": \"a typically sustained attack\", \"from\": 6408, \"to\": 6436}, {\"ngram\": \"a string\", \"from\": 6469, \"to\": 6477}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 6481, \"to\": 6487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only Viviani and Mullen could survive on the front by this point as they fended off a peloton already reduced to just 70 riders, and Healy and Alexey Lutsenko (Kazakhstan) joined forces to try and bridge across.\", \"from\": 6501, \"to\": 6712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6518, \"end\": 6524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999998279554495, \"rank\": 1.544359642084208e-07, \"text\": \"Mullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 6644, \"end\": 6659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexey_Lutsenko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexey Lutsenko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexey_Lutsenko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexey_Lutsenko\"}, {\"begin\": 6661, \"end\": 6671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.1960097064722487e-11, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Only Viviani\", \"from\": 6501, \"to\": 6513}, {\"ngram\": \"the front\", \"from\": 6542, \"to\": 6551}, {\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 6555, \"to\": 6565}, {\"ngram\": \"a peloton\", \"from\": 6585, \"to\": 6594}, {\"ngram\": \"just 70 riders\", \"from\": 6614, \"to\": 6628}, {\"ngram\": \"Healy\", \"from\": 6634, \"to\": 6639}, {\"ngram\": \"forces\", \"from\": 6680, \"to\": 6686}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Healy's determined pursuit quickly hacked 30 seconds off his teammate's advantage in the break and provided the foundations for a deftly forged early two-man ambush by the Irish squad.\", \"from\": 6713, \"to\": 6897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6885, \"end\": 6890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999055358894452, \"rank\": 9.331359468347277e-05, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Healy's determined pursuit\", \"from\": 6713, \"to\": 6739}, {\"ngram\": \"30 seconds\", \"from\": 6755, \"to\": 6765}, {\"ngram\": \"his teammate's advantage\", \"from\": 6770, \"to\": 6794}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 6798, \"to\": 6807}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundations\", \"from\": 6821, \"to\": 6836}, {\"ngram\": \"a deftly forged early two-man ambush\", \"from\": 6841, \"to\": 6877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, Viviani, suffering from cramps, had to sit up on the C\\u00f4te de Bievres, one of the toughest climbs of the entire course.\", \"from\": 6898, \"to\": 7029, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contrast\", \"from\": 6901, \"to\": 6909}, {\"ngram\": \"Viviani\", \"from\": 6911, \"to\": 6918}, {\"ngram\": \"cramps\", \"from\": 6935, \"to\": 6941}, {\"ngram\": \"the C\\u00f4te de Bievres\", \"from\": 6960, \"to\": 6979}, {\"ngram\": \"the toughest climbs\", \"from\": 6988, \"to\": 7007}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire course\", \"from\": 7011, \"to\": 7028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The peloton was growing increasingly unstable too, mainly thanks to Tiesj Benoot winding things up steadily on the Bievres cimb and Evenepoel shadowing him closely.\", \"from\": 7031, \"to\": 7195, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The peloton\", \"from\": 7031, \"to\": 7042}, {\"ngram\": \"Tiesj Benoot winding things\", \"from\": 7099, \"to\": 7126}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bievres cimb\", \"from\": 7142, \"to\": 7158}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 7163, \"to\": 7172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Healy and Mullen joined forces just over the top, with Mullen emptying himself for his teammate and Lutsenko before dropping back, but the rest of the field was less than 20 seconds behind.\", \"from\": 7196, \"to\": 7385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7206, \"end\": 7212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999998279554495, \"rank\": 1.544359642084208e-07, \"text\": \"Mullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 7251, \"end\": 7257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999998279554495, \"rank\": 1.544359642084208e-07, \"text\": \"Mullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Healy\", \"from\": 7196, \"to\": 7201}, {\"ngram\": \"forces\", \"from\": 7220, \"to\": 7226}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 7237, \"to\": 7244}, {\"ngram\": \"his teammate\", \"from\": 7279, \"to\": 7291}, {\"ngram\": \"Lutsenko\", \"from\": 7296, \"to\": 7304}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 7331, \"to\": 7339}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 7343, \"to\": 7352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first of two blistering test moves by Evenepoel all but dragged the pack up to the trio of breakaways, but Healy, however, was still motoring strongly.\", \"from\": 7387, \"to\": 7542, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two blistering test moves\", \"from\": 7400, \"to\": 7425}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 7429, \"to\": 7438}, {\"ngram\": \"the pack\", \"from\": 7455, \"to\": 7463}, {\"ngram\": \"the trio\", \"from\": 7470, \"to\": 7478}, {\"ngram\": \"breakaways\", \"from\": 7482, \"to\": 7492}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then as Evenepoel eased, shaking his head, the Irishman's bold persistence, boosted by some support from Lutsenko was quickly rewarded with a renewed 30-second gap.\", \"from\": 7543, \"to\": 7707, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 7551, \"to\": 7560}, {\"ngram\": \"his head\", \"from\": 7576, \"to\": 7584}, {\"ngram\": \"the Irishman's bold persistence\", \"from\": 7586, \"to\": 7617}, {\"ngram\": \"some support\", \"from\": 7630, \"to\": 7642}, {\"ngram\": \"Lutsenko\", \"from\": 7648, \"to\": 7656}, {\"ngram\": \"a renewed 30-second gap\", \"from\": 7683, \"to\": 7706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The race roared back into Paris and with 60km to go, the indefatigable Novak made a third move, only for Nils Politt (Germany) to come over the top, followed by France's Valentin Madouas, Fred Wright (Great Britain) and Canada's Michael Woods.\", \"from\": 7709, \"to\": 7952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7735, \"end\": 7740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8696011185640274e-35, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 7870, \"end\": 7876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9968804645448817, \"rank\": 0.0031256625369655306, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7879, \"end\": 7895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valentin Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 7897, \"end\": 7908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999956969842781, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Wright\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 7910, \"end\": 7923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9984078814829216, \"rank\": 0.001594652234714316, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 7929, \"end\": 7935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999991732842097, \"rank\": 8.2671631478097e-07, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 7938, \"end\": 7951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Woods_(DJ)\", \"score\": 0.6748750082202509, \"rank\": 0.33912275537233105, \"text\": \"Michael Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Woods_(DJ)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Woods_(DJ)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The race\", \"from\": 7709, \"to\": 7717}, {\"ngram\": \"60km\", \"from\": 7750, \"to\": 7754}, {\"ngram\": \"the indefatigable Novak\", \"from\": 7762, \"to\": 7785}, {\"ngram\": \"a third move\", \"from\": 7791, \"to\": 7803}, {\"ngram\": \"Nils Politt\", \"from\": 7814, \"to\": 7825}, {\"ngram\": \"(Germany\", \"from\": 7826, \"to\": 7834}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 7849, \"to\": 7856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That sparked a brief moment of hesitation and even when the four chasers were suddenly joined by Stefan K\\u00fcng (Switzerland), Mongolia's Jambaljamants Sainbayar and Marco Haller (Austria), for some reason the warning lights still failed to come on in the peloton.\", \"from\": 7953, \"to\": 8214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8050, \"end\": 8061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_K\\u00fcng\", \"score\": 0.9999998054609212, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefan K\\u00fcng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_K\\u00fcng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_K\\u00fcng\"}, {\"begin\": 8063, \"end\": 8074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.999961479062934, \"rank\": 3.8521633085104684e-05, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 8077, \"end\": 8085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mongolia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.999797165118631e-15, \"text\": \"Mongolia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mongolia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mongolia\"}, {\"begin\": 8116, \"end\": 8128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Haller_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999960452229046, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marco Haller\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Haller_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Haller_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 8130, \"end\": 8137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.9982058107969345, \"rank\": 0.0017950891173045406, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brief moment\", \"from\": 7966, \"to\": 7980}, {\"ngram\": \"hesitation\", \"from\": 7984, \"to\": 7994}, {\"ngram\": \"the four chasers\", \"from\": 8009, \"to\": 8025}, {\"ngram\": \"Sainbayar\", \"from\": 8102, \"to\": 8111}, {\"ngram\": \"some reason\", \"from\": 8144, \"to\": 8155}, {\"ngram\": \"the warning lights\", \"from\": 8156, \"to\": 8174}, {\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 8202, \"to\": 8213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This absence of commitment in the bunch could have been disastrous for Evenepoel and company as all three major teams - Belgium, Denmark and Holland - had missed out on the dangerous move, whose advantage quickly spiralled north of a minute.\", \"from\": 8216, \"to\": 8458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8337, \"end\": 8344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.436398602191839e-12, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 8346, \"end\": 8353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.999999344642889, \"rank\": 6.55357217646797e-07, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 8358, \"end\": 8365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999953803569337, \"rank\": 4.619664456446929e-06, \"text\": \"Holland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This absence\", \"from\": 8216, \"to\": 8228}, {\"ngram\": \"commitment\", \"from\": 8232, \"to\": 8242}, {\"ngram\": \"the bunch\", \"from\": 8246, \"to\": 8255}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 8287, \"to\": 8296}, {\"ngram\": \"company\", \"from\": 8301, \"to\": 8308}, {\"ngram\": \"all three major teams\", \"from\": 8312, \"to\": 8333}, {\"ngram\": \"the dangerous move\", \"from\": 8385, \"to\": 8403}, {\"ngram\": \"whose advantage\", \"from\": 8405, \"to\": 8420}, {\"ngram\": \"a minute\", \"from\": 8448, \"to\": 8456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tireless Benoot was the first to try and spur some life back into the hesitant peloton.\", \"from\": 8460, \"to\": 8551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8473, \"end\": 8479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiesj_Benoot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Benoot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiesj_Benoot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiesj_Benoot\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some life\", \"from\": 8510, \"to\": 8519}, {\"ngram\": \"the hesitant peloton\", \"from\": 8530, \"to\": 8550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when Van Aert dropped back to talk to the Belgian team manager just when another strong four-rider team, Slovenia, saw their leader Matej Mohoric, suffer a mechanical and Denmark's main man, Mads Pedersen indicated he had a puncture, the race was close to seeing a surprise breakaway gain the upper hand.\", \"from\": 8552, \"to\": 8860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8598, \"end\": 8605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.149028046004699e-13, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 8661, \"end\": 8669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"score\": 0.999678333617366, \"rank\": 0.000321769885363485, \"text\": \"Slovenia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovenia\"}, {\"begin\": 8688, \"end\": 8701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matej_Mohori\\u010d\", \"score\": 0.9999999955807652, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matej Mohoric\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matej_Mohori\\u010d\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matej_Mohori\\u010d\"}, {\"begin\": 8727, \"end\": 8734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.999999344642889, \"rank\": 6.55357217646797e-07, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 8747, \"end\": 8760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9973584045699821, \"rank\": 0.0026481297583575304, \"text\": \"Mads Pedersen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Aert\", \"from\": 8561, \"to\": 8569}, {\"ngram\": \"another strong four-rider team\", \"from\": 8629, \"to\": 8659}, {\"ngram\": \"their leader\", \"from\": 8675, \"to\": 8687}, {\"ngram\": \"a puncture\", \"from\": 8778, \"to\": 8788}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 8790, \"to\": 8798}, {\"ngram\": \"a surprise breakaway\", \"from\": 8819, \"to\": 8839}, {\"ngram\": \"the upper hand\", \"from\": 8845, \"to\": 8859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Healy was still giving it everything as he and Lutsenko swung right onto the cobbles of the decisive C\\u00f4te de la Butte Montmartre for the first of three times and the Irishman went solo at 46km to go on the steeper part of the ascent.\", \"from\": 8862, \"to\": 9095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8980, \"end\": 8990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5336169978655607e-23, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Healy\", \"from\": 8862, \"to\": 8867}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 8888, \"to\": 8898}, {\"ngram\": \"Lutsenko\", \"from\": 8909, \"to\": 8917}, {\"ngram\": \"the cobbles\", \"from\": 8935, \"to\": 8946}, {\"ngram\": \"three times\", \"from\": 9008, \"to\": 9019}, {\"ngram\": \"the Irishman\", \"from\": 9024, \"to\": 9036}, {\"ngram\": \"46km\", \"from\": 9050, \"to\": 9054}, {\"ngram\": \"the steeper part\", \"from\": 9064, \"to\": 9080}, {\"ngram\": \"the ascent\", \"from\": 9084, \"to\": 9094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But behind an even more dramatic moment was occurring simultaneously as Van der Poel launched a ferocious move in the pack, and Van Aert equally quickly went with him.\", \"from\": 9096, \"to\": 9263, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an even more dramatic moment\", \"from\": 9107, \"to\": 9135}, {\"ngram\": \"Van der\", \"from\": 9168, \"to\": 9175}, {\"ngram\": \"Poel\", \"from\": 9176, \"to\": 9180}, {\"ngram\": \"a ferocious move\", \"from\": 9190, \"to\": 9206}, {\"ngram\": \"the pack\", \"from\": 9210, \"to\": 9218}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Aert\", \"from\": 9224, \"to\": 9232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matteo Jorgenson (USA) then bridged across to the Belgian and Dutchman with around half a dozen more riders, also containing Skujins and Alaphilippe forming a chase group.\", \"from\": 9265, \"to\": 9436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9283, \"end\": 9286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 6.917058918488637e-12, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 9315, \"end\": 9322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.149028046004699e-13, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 9327, \"end\": 9335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999237229810596, \"rank\": 7.62812571813139e-05, \"text\": \"Dutchman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 9390, \"end\": 9397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toms_Skuji\\u0146\\u0161\", \"score\": 0.9740059610041658, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Skujins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toms_Skuji\\u0146\\u0161\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toms_Skuji\\u0146\\u0161\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Matteo Jorgenson\", \"from\": 9265, \"to\": 9281}, {\"ngram\": \"around half a dozen more riders\", \"from\": 9341, \"to\": 9372}, {\"ngram\": \"Alaphilippe\", \"from\": 9402, \"to\": 9413}, {\"ngram\": \"a chase group\", \"from\": 9422, \"to\": 9435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The entire gap between lone rider Healy and the 40-strong peloton, though, still including Evenepoel, was only 57 seconds with 40 kilometres to go, making for a very unpredictable, volatile scenario.\", \"from\": 9437, \"to\": 9636, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The entire gap\", \"from\": 9437, \"to\": 9451}, {\"ngram\": \"lone rider Healy\", \"from\": 9460, \"to\": 9476}, {\"ngram\": \"the 40-strong peloton\", \"from\": 9481, \"to\": 9502}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 9528, \"to\": 9537}, {\"ngram\": \"only 57 seconds\", \"from\": 9543, \"to\": 9558}, {\"ngram\": \"40 kilometres\", \"from\": 9564, \"to\": 9577}, {\"ngram\": \"a very unpredictable, volatile scenario\", \"from\": 9596, \"to\": 9635}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pedersen then dragged the remnants of the peloton back up to the Van der Poel group, only for Evenepoel to take the race by the scruff of its neck for the first time and soar away solo up to the chasers behind Healy.\", \"from\": 9638, \"to\": 9854, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pedersen\", \"from\": 9638, \"to\": 9646}, {\"ngram\": \"the remnants\", \"from\": 9660, \"to\": 9672}, {\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 9676, \"to\": 9687}, {\"ngram\": \"the Van der Poel group\", \"from\": 9699, \"to\": 9721}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 9732, \"to\": 9741}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 9750, \"to\": 9758}, {\"ngram\": \"the scruff\", \"from\": 9762, \"to\": 9772}, {\"ngram\": \"its neck\", \"from\": 9776, \"to\": 9784}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 9789, \"to\": 9803}, {\"ngram\": \"the chasers\", \"from\": 9829, \"to\": 9840}, {\"ngram\": \"Healy\", \"from\": 9848, \"to\": 9853}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Compared to the other seven counter-attackers, Evenepoel's power was simply electrifying, and it felt like only a matter of time the Belgian opted to go clear.\", \"from\": 9856, \"to\": 10015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9989, \"end\": 9996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.149028046004699e-13, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other seven counter\", \"from\": 9868, \"to\": 9891}, {\"ngram\": \"attackers\", \"from\": 9892, \"to\": 9901}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel's power\", \"from\": 9903, \"to\": 9920}, {\"ngram\": \"only a matter\", \"from\": 9963, \"to\": 9976}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 9980, \"to\": 9984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First though, he turned in another driving acceleration, tearing his way up an unclassified climb and forcing his opponents to fall in line.\", \"from\": 10016, \"to\": 10156, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another driving acceleration\", \"from\": 10043, \"to\": 10071}, {\"ngram\": \"his way\", \"from\": 10081, \"to\": 10088}, {\"ngram\": \"an unclassified climb\", \"from\": 10092, \"to\": 10113}, {\"ngram\": \"his opponents\", \"from\": 10126, \"to\": 10139}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 10151, \"to\": 10155}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such was his strength that by the time Healy - after 60 kilometres away - was finally caught, the lead break had shrunk to just the Belgian, Madouas, K\\u00fcng and Marco Haller (Austria).\", \"from\": 10157, \"to\": 10339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10289, \"end\": 10296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.149028046004699e-13, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 10298, \"end\": 10305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 10316, \"end\": 10328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Haller_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999960452229046, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marco Haller\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Haller_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marco_Haller_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 10330, \"end\": 10337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.9982058107969345, \"rank\": 0.0017950891173045406, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his strength\", \"from\": 10166, \"to\": 10178}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 10187, \"to\": 10195}, {\"ngram\": \"Healy\", \"from\": 10196, \"to\": 10201}, {\"ngram\": \"60 kilometres\", \"from\": 10210, \"to\": 10223}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead break\", \"from\": 10251, \"to\": 10265}, {\"ngram\": \"K\\u00fcng\", \"from\": 10307, \"to\": 10311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Come the second ascent of the Butte Montmartre, another crushing acceleration by the Belgian squeezed the break down to Madouas and Evenepoel while Van der Poel began a much more explosive charge behind.\", \"from\": 10341, \"to\": 10544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10377, \"end\": 10387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.5336169978655607e-23, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}, {\"begin\": 10426, \"end\": 10433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.149028046004699e-13, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 10461, \"end\": 10468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the second ascent\", \"from\": 10346, \"to\": 10363}, {\"ngram\": \"another crushing acceleration\", \"from\": 10389, \"to\": 10418}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 10443, \"to\": 10452}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 10473, \"to\": 10482}, {\"ngram\": \"Van der Poel\", \"from\": 10489, \"to\": 10501}, {\"ngram\": \"a much more explosive charge\", \"from\": 10508, \"to\": 10536}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Aert, though, instantly latched onto the Dutchman's back wheel, while a an unleashed Evenepoel forged onwards, with only Madouas, willing to collaborate for at least the chance of a silver medal, for company.\", \"from\": 10545, \"to\": 10757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10670, \"end\": 10677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Aert\", \"from\": 10545, \"to\": 10553}, {\"ngram\": \"the Dutchman's back wheel\", \"from\": 10586, \"to\": 10611}, {\"ngram\": \"a an unleashed Evenepoel\", \"from\": 10619, \"to\": 10643}, {\"ngram\": \"at least the chance\", \"from\": 10706, \"to\": 10725}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 10729, \"to\": 10743}, {\"ngram\": \"company\", \"from\": 10749, \"to\": 10756}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Knowing how fast Madouas can be in a two-up sprint, Evenepoel still had more than enough in the tank to ensure the gap widened to a minute, with Van Aert marking everything behind.\", \"from\": 10759, \"to\": 10939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10776, \"end\": 10783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a two-up sprint\", \"from\": 10794, \"to\": 10809}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 10811, \"to\": 10820}, {\"ngram\": \"the tank\", \"from\": 10851, \"to\": 10859}, {\"ngram\": \"the gap\", \"from\": 10870, \"to\": 10877}, {\"ngram\": \"a minute\", \"from\": 10889, \"to\": 10897}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Aert\", \"from\": 10904, \"to\": 10912}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 10921, \"to\": 10931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By this point the battle for gold was almost certainly down to just the two and 15km from the finish, Evenepoel made sure there would be no duel for the top spot, as he used a steadily rising little climb to leave the Frenchman behind.\", \"from\": 10940, \"to\": 11176, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 10943, \"to\": 10953}, {\"ngram\": \"the battle\", \"from\": 10954, \"to\": 10964}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 10969, \"to\": 10973}, {\"ngram\": \"just the two and 15km\", \"from\": 11003, \"to\": 11024}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 11030, \"to\": 11040}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 11042, \"to\": 11051}, {\"ngram\": \"no duel\", \"from\": 11077, \"to\": 11084}, {\"ngram\": \"the top spot\", \"from\": 11089, \"to\": 11101}, {\"ngram\": \"a steadily rising little climb\", \"from\": 11114, \"to\": 11144}, {\"ngram\": \"the Frenchman\", \"from\": 11154, \"to\": 11167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It all looked to be over bar the shouting as Evenepoel stormed over the top of the Montmartre, with his advantage on his closest pursuer, rising to nearly a minute.\", \"from\": 11178, \"to\": 11342, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bar\", \"from\": 11203, \"to\": 11206}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 11223, \"to\": 11232}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 11246, \"to\": 11253}, {\"ngram\": \"the Montmartre\", \"from\": 11257, \"to\": 11271}, {\"ngram\": \"his advantage\", \"from\": 11278, \"to\": 11291}, {\"ngram\": \"his closest pursuer\", \"from\": 11295, \"to\": 11314}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly a minute\", \"from\": 11326, \"to\": 11341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But even as he shot down the other side and onto the final flat section leading towards the Eiffel Tower, the Belgian's increasingly pale pallor and worried looks suggested that something could be up.\", \"from\": 11343, \"to\": 11543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11453, \"end\": 11460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 5.149028046004699e-13, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other side\", \"from\": 11368, \"to\": 11382}, {\"ngram\": \"the final flat section\", \"from\": 11392, \"to\": 11414}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 11431, \"to\": 11447}, {\"ngram\": \"worried looks\", \"from\": 11492, \"to\": 11505}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 11521, \"to\": 11530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then with around four kilometres to go, confirmation that a last-minute disaster could be looming arrived as the Evenepoel skidded to a stop, quickly placed his punctured bike on the lefthand side of the road and spinning round to face the oncoming race, began yelling loudly at his support car for a replacement.\", \"from\": 11545, \"to\": 11858, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"around four kilometres\", \"from\": 11555, \"to\": 11577}, {\"ngram\": \"a last-minute disaster\", \"from\": 11603, \"to\": 11625}, {\"ngram\": \"the Evenepoel\", \"from\": 11654, \"to\": 11667}, {\"ngram\": \"a stop\", \"from\": 11679, \"to\": 11685}, {\"ngram\": \"his punctured bike\", \"from\": 11702, \"to\": 11720}, {\"ngram\": \"the lefthand side\", \"from\": 11724, \"to\": 11741}, {\"ngram\": \"the road\", \"from\": 11745, \"to\": 11753}, {\"ngram\": \"round\", \"from\": 11767, \"to\": 11772}, {\"ngram\": \"the oncoming race\", \"from\": 11781, \"to\": 11798}, {\"ngram\": \"his support car\", \"from\": 11824, \"to\": 11839}, {\"ngram\": \"a replacement\", \"from\": 11844, \"to\": 11857}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fortunately for his chances, the changeover proved a relatively quick one and after a lengthy push from his mechanic he was soon en route again.\", \"from\": 11860, \"to\": 12004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his chances\", \"from\": 11876, \"to\": 11887}, {\"ngram\": \"the changeover\", \"from\": 11889, \"to\": 11903}, {\"ngram\": \"a lengthy push\", \"from\": 11944, \"to\": 11958}, {\"ngram\": \"his mechanic\", \"from\": 11964, \"to\": 11976}, {\"ngram\": \"route\", \"from\": 11992, \"to\": 11997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the lack of race radios meant Evenepoel had no idea of how much time he still in hand and it was really only as he turned the final right-hand corner to finish under the Eiffel Tower itself that the look of frantic concern turned into a definitive victory smile.\", \"from\": 12005, \"to\": 12276, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the lack\", \"from\": 12014, \"to\": 12022}, {\"ngram\": \"race radios\", \"from\": 12026, \"to\": 12037}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 12044, \"to\": 12053}, {\"ngram\": \"no idea\", \"from\": 12058, \"to\": 12065}, {\"ngram\": \"hand\", \"from\": 12095, \"to\": 12099}, {\"ngram\": \"the final right-hand corner\", \"from\": 12136, \"to\": 12163}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 12180, \"to\": 12196}, {\"ngram\": \"the look\", \"from\": 12209, \"to\": 12217}, {\"ngram\": \"frantic concern\", \"from\": 12221, \"to\": 12236}, {\"ngram\": \"a definitive victory smile\", \"from\": 12249, \"to\": 12275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Crossing the line, Evenepoel ground to a halt and dismounted in the centre of the finish line, celebrating one of his most memorable triumphs - and there have been plenty of those in his six year career - with outflung arms and a skyward glance.\", \"from\": 12278, \"to\": 12525, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 12287, \"to\": 12295}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 12297, \"to\": 12306}, {\"ngram\": \"a halt\", \"from\": 12317, \"to\": 12323}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 12342, \"to\": 12352}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 12356, \"to\": 12371}, {\"ngram\": \"his most memorable triumphs\", \"from\": 12392, \"to\": 12419}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 12442, \"to\": 12448}, {\"ngram\": \"his six year career\", \"from\": 12461, \"to\": 12480}, {\"ngram\": \"outflung arms\", \"from\": 12488, \"to\": 12501}, {\"ngram\": \"a skyward glance\", \"from\": 12506, \"to\": 12522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His ostentatious victory salute was certainly justified: in one fell swoop, Evenepoel had just become the first male rider ever to secure gold in both road race and time trial Olympic categories.\", \"from\": 12526, \"to\": 12721, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His ostentatious victory salute\", \"from\": 12526, \"to\": 12557}, {\"ngram\": \"one fell swoop\", \"from\": 12586, \"to\": 12600}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 12602, \"to\": 12611}, {\"ngram\": \"the first male rider\", \"from\": 12628, \"to\": 12648}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 12664, \"to\": 12668}, {\"ngram\": \"both road race and time trial Olympic categories\", \"from\": 12672, \"to\": 12720}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All this, too, has happened just two weeks after Evenepoel took his first ever podium in his first ever Tour de France.\", \"from\": 12723, \"to\": 12842, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 12772, \"to\": 12781}, {\"ngram\": \"his first ever podium\", \"from\": 12787, \"to\": 12808}, {\"ngram\": \"his first ever Tour de France\", \"from\": 12812, \"to\": 12841}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Olympics are another massive moment of cycling success this summer for Evenepoel to savour, and while at just 24, there will surely be plenty more to come, this one is a win that will surely be remembered as a crowning moment of his entire career.\", \"from\": 12843, \"to\": 13098, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 12847, \"to\": 12859}, {\"ngram\": \"another massive moment\", \"from\": 12864, \"to\": 12886}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 12898, \"to\": 12905}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 12922, \"to\": 12931}, {\"ngram\": \"savour\", \"from\": 12935, \"to\": 12941}, {\"ngram\": \"this one\", \"from\": 13007, \"to\": 13015}, {\"ngram\": \"a win\", \"from\": 13019, \"to\": 13024}, {\"ngram\": \"a crowning moment\", \"from\": 13059, \"to\": 13076}, {\"ngram\": \"his entire career\", \"from\": 13080, \"to\": 13097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Results powered byFirstCycling Get unlimited access to all of our coverage of the 2024 Tour de France Femmes - including breaking news and analysis reported by our journalists on the ground from every stage as it happens and more.Find out more.\", \"from\": 13100, \"to\": 13345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Results\", \"from\": 13100, \"to\": 13107}, {\"ngram\": \"unlimited access\", \"from\": 13135, \"to\": 13151}, {\"ngram\": \"our coverage\", \"from\": 13162, \"to\": 13174}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Tour de France Femmes\", \"from\": 13178, \"to\": 13208}, {\"ngram\": \"breaking news\", \"from\": 13221, \"to\": 13234}, {\"ngram\": \"analysis\", \"from\": 13239, \"to\": 13247}, {\"ngram\": \"our journalists\", \"from\": 13260, \"to\": 13275}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 13279, \"to\": 13289}, {\"ngram\": \"every stage\", \"from\": 13295, \"to\": 13306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alasdair Fotheringham has been reporting on cycling since 1991.\", \"from\": 13347, \"to\": 13410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13347, \"end\": 13368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alasdair_Fotheringham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alasdair Fotheringham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q1930187\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alasdair_Fotheringham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alasdair_Fotheringham\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cycling\", \"from\": 13391, \"to\": 13398}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has covered every Tour de France since 1992 bar one, as well as numerous other bike races of all shapes and sizes, ranging from the Olympic Games in 2008 to the now sadly defunct Subida a Urkiola hill climb in Spain.\", \"from\": 13411, \"to\": 13630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13432, \"end\": 13446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.393944375869676e-22, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 13624, \"end\": 13629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999999872731686, \"rank\": 1.272223527484887e-07, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"numerous other bike races\", \"from\": 13478, \"to\": 13503}, {\"ngram\": \"all shapes\", \"from\": 13507, \"to\": 13517}, {\"ngram\": \"sizes\", \"from\": 13522, \"to\": 13527}, {\"ngram\": \"th